{"schema_version":"signalforge/research-case-export/v1","exported_at":"2026-07-22T11:46:56.077670767Z","summary":{"case_id":"case-request-019f899e-4e5f-7b15-920d-4d65130f2d66","run_id":"run-019f899e-4e5f-7b15-920d-4d65130f2d66","title":"microsoft / nvidia research case","as_of":"2026-07-21T16:00:00Z","intent":"company_comparison","saved_at":"2026-07-22T11:40:42.695931897Z","evidence_items":14,"calculation_receipts":16,"projection_sha256":"7116cf267680e937222f7a6a834ddd424c0a5488fdfa69df26775428242dd7ed"},"case":{"schema_version":"signalforge/research-workspace/v1","case_id":"case-request-019f899e-4e5f-7b15-920d-4d65130f2d66","run_id":"run-019f899e-4e5f-7b15-920d-4d65130f2d66","request_id":"request-019f899e-4e5f-7b15-920d-4d65130f2d66","status":"completed","title":"microsoft / nvidia research case","question":"Compare Microsoft and NVIDIA as long-term businesses. Include business quality, accounting comparability, financial quality, market behavior, DCF valuation ranges, multiples, explicit assumptions, counterevidence, and thesis invalidation conditions. Evaluate the explicit scenario of higher-for-longer interest rates and slower AI infrastructure spending.","as_of":"2026-07-21T16:00:00Z","intent":"company_comparison","companies":[{"entity_id":"sec-cik:0000789019","label":"microsoft"},{"entity_id":"sec-cik:0001045810","label":"nvidia"}],"sections":[{"section_type":"comparison","title":"Comparison","content":"Microsoft generates revenue through cloud solutions, software licensing, online advertising, and devices. NVIDIA operates as a full-stack computing infrastructure company including GPUs, networking, and software. Microsoft plans continued capital expenditures for AI infrastructure and datacenter growth. NVIDIA maintains significant long-term supply and capacity obligations, including commitments for Blackwell introductions. NVIDIA's revenue is derived from a limited number of direct customers, primarily in Compute and Networking. Business-model evidence, reporting comparability, and receipt-backed financial quality are considered together. Differing fiscal-period boundaries constrain direct historical comparison.\n\nVerified numerical disclosure: NVDA and MSFT margin were not compared (period identity differs: FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26 versus FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30; no direction was released). MSFT and NVDA cash conversion were not compared (period identity differs: FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30 versus FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26; no direction was released). NVDA and MSFT free cash flow were not compared (period identity differs: FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26 versus FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30; no direction was released). MSFT and NVDA growth rate were not compared (period identity differs: FY2024-FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30 versus FY2024-FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26; no direction was released). MSFT and NVDA capex intensity were not compared (period identity differs: FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30 versus FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26; no direction was released).","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-01-001","claim-context-request-context-01-002","claim-context-request-context-01-003","claim-context-request-context-01-004","claim-context-request-context-02-001","claim-context-request-context-02-004","claim-context-request-context-02-005","claim-context-request-context-02-006","claim-context-request-context-06-001","claim-context-request-context-06-007","claim-context-request-context-02-007","claim-context-request-context-02-008","claim-context-request-context-02-009","claim-context-request-context-02-010","claim-context-request-context-02-011"],"evidence_refs":["msft-business-model","nvda-business-model","msft-capex","nvda-supply-commitments","nvda-customer-concentration","comparison:fiscal-period-boundary"],"receipt_refs":["receipt-6dd3c1bfc1f05b8bd0cb","receipt-8569297db9f5120b39af","receipt-40c013fa18091fb6750c","receipt-cf0b07677c42d2424959","receipt-596f606d38443034525f","receipt-5a2136eb61695e5d7624","receipt-74a202237ae7e9f97014","receipt-8a299dd8150a0981dd4c","receipt-949931ccd6fd3c6c31e2","receipt-99a6312597bbf9e92996"],"numerical_refs":["numrel-20d5854a82cab8fe8e70","numrel-6bb2e1736559685ad76e","numrel-9700c524641d17c620fc","numrel-f20096599344cb51a102","numrel-fd1d2dce733f33c4f29c"]},{"section_type":"transmission_mechanisms","title":"Transmission Mechanisms","content":"A scenario of slower AI infrastructure spending could impact NVIDIA's Data Center revenue growth and may influence Microsoft's capital expenditure decisions. Under the explicit higher-rate scenario, a higher discount-rate input would reduce otherwise identical present-value outputs. Under the explicit slower-spending scenario, lower demand could pressure utilization, margins, or inventory. Transmission is presented as a conditional scenario mechanism. Macro transmission remains anchored to issuer-disclosed currency, rate, export-control, or supply-chain risk.\n\nThese mechanisms are scenario-conditioned pathways, not estimates of observed causality.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-03-002","claim-context-request-context-03-003","claim-context-request-context-03-004","claim-context-request-context-01-005"],"evidence_refs":["nvda-presentation-demand-framing","msft-capex","nvda-rate-risk"]},{"section_type":"market_measurement","title":"Market Measurement","content":"Official point-in-time exchange closes are available for both MSFT and NVDA. Market observations are measurements, not causal attributions.\n\nPrice co-movement, correlation, and event-window timing do not by themselves establish causality.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-05-002","claim-context-request-context-05-003"],"evidence_refs":["market-price:msft","market-price:nvda"]},{"section_type":"scenarios","title":"Scenarios","content":"In a higher-for-longer interest rate environment, the fair value of NVIDIA's investment portfolio may be impacted. A scenario of slower AI infrastructure spending could be exacerbated by semiconductor export controls restricting NVIDIA sales. Scenario ranges combine Go-validated valuation receipts with the explicit macro assumptions.\n\nVerified numerical disclosure: NVDA and MSFT free cash flow were not compared (period identity differs: FY2025 2024-01-29 to 2025-01-26 versus FY2025 2024-07-01 to 2025-06-30; no direction was released). MSFT multiple was 29.49x, lower than NVDA at 69.14x for 2026-07-20..FY2025 as of 2026-07-21, a deterministic difference of 39.65x. NVDA enterprise value was USD 1.21 trillion, lower than MSFT at USD 1.52 trillion for FY2026-FY2030 as of 2026-07-21, a deterministic difference of USD 311.4 billion.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-01-005","claim-context-request-context-01-006","claim-context-request-context-03-002","claim-context-request-context-03-003","claim-context-request-context-03-004","claim-context-request-context-04-001","claim-context-request-context-04-002","claim-context-request-context-04-003"],"evidence_refs":["nvda-rate-risk","nvda-export-controls","nvda-presentation-demand-framing","msft-capex"],"receipt_refs":["receipt-e404924433528cbff056","receipt-f8ae461e2f57b44df3e6","receipt-197224c9e5402cf57437","receipt-83fb4e77f33bc9aa5426","receipt-3632130c8601e7ddc5df","receipt-a38845ab1c40091e9bcf"],"numerical_refs":["numrel-4ef15b494fdf51717403","numrel-b3e5dbdce197037e6675","numrel-e299a42cb20606041bcb"]},{"section_type":"counterevidence","title":"Counterevidence","content":"NVIDIA's fiscal 2025 inventory provisions had an unfavorable effect on gross margins. AI semiconductor export controls can restrict NVIDIA sales, impair demand, disrupt supply and distribution, advantage competitors, and create excess inventory charges.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-01-007","claim-context-request-context-01-008","claim-context-request-context-01-009","claim-context-request-context-04-006","claim-context-request-context-06-004","claim-context-request-context-06-006"],"evidence_refs":["nvda-inventory-risk","msft-cloud-margin","nvda-export-controls"]},{"section_type":"invalidation_conditions","title":"Invalidation Conditions","content":"The thesis is invalidated if semiconductor export controls restrict NVIDIA sales or if slower AI infrastructure spending leads to significant inventory pressure or margin contraction.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-01-005","claim-context-request-context-01-006","claim-context-request-context-01-009","claim-context-request-context-03-004"],"evidence_refs":["nvda-rate-risk","nvda-export-controls"]},{"section_type":"evidence","title":"Evidence","content":"Evidence includes regulatory filings for Microsoft's business model, capital expenditures, and cloud margins, as well as NVIDIA's business model, supply commitments, and customer concentration.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-01-001","claim-context-request-context-01-002","claim-context-request-context-01-003","claim-context-request-context-01-004","claim-context-request-context-02-001","claim-context-request-context-02-002","claim-context-request-context-02-003","claim-context-request-context-02-004"],"evidence_refs":["msft-business-model","nvda-business-model","msft-capex","nvda-supply-commitments","msft-cash-flow","msft-cloud-margin"]},{"section_type":"limitations","title":"Limitations","content":"Exact concurrent calendar-period comparability is unavailable due to non-concurrent fiscal year endings. Specific accounting comparability metrics and financial quality ratios were not provided in the authorized material. Market behavior metrics (volatility, beta, correlation) were not provided. Business quality metrics (non-qualitative) were not provided.","claim_refs":["claim-context-request-context-06-007"],"evidence_refs":["comparison:fiscal-period-boundary"]}],"evidence":[{"evidence_id":"comparison:fiscal-period-boundary","source_type":"deterministic_scope_check","locator":"fixture:golden/financial-sna